# Ex1 Anti-Patterns

See `docs/ex1-mistakes.md`. Ex1 grade 76 — algorithm OK, C++ hygiene and runtime need work.

## Never repeat

| Pattern | Code |
|---------|------|
| `namespace su = mp_units::...` inside functions | e17s |
| `ScanProbing`, `ScanOptions`, `TickSnapshot` with raw doubles | e16n |
| `ErrorLogger::lines()` exposing internal vector | e22m |
| `SimulationState::setTruthCell` — unneeded public API | e08m |
| Non-const `scan()` when read-only | e07m |
| Slow runs on small maps | b05s |
| Missing file → no error handling | b06m |
| Deferred error flush at end of run (`flushIfNeeded`) | ex2 violation — log immediately per run |

## Do not port

`ScanProbing`, `TickSnapshot`, `SimulationState`, ex1 `ErrorLogger` (deferred flush or `lines()`), ex1 `main` loop (whole-program abort), txt parsers.

## Safe to reuse ideas

Frontier/BFS → `MappingAlgorithmImpl::nextStep`; collision checks → `MockMovement`; scoring math → `MapsComparison`.

---

## ⚠️ Algorithm behavioral contract — do not "port and assume it works"

The biggest porting trap is treating the algorithm as "structure ported = done." Ex1's exploration worked because **scanning, fusion, and footprint together guaranteed a passable local bubble before planning**. Each of those three things maps differently in ex2:

| Ex1 behavior | Ex2 reality | What breaks if ignored |
|---|---|---|
| `SphericalScanner::scan()` fires full hemisphere **in one tick** before planning | One orientation per `nextStep` step — full pass spread over many steps | Adjacent cells stay `Unmapped` after a coarse pass → `isSpherePassable` fails → drone never moves |
| `proximity_max` fusion cap (~20 cm bubble) per shot | `ScanResultToVoxels` (instructor-provided) fuses along full ray to `z_max` on miss — different semantics | Not a blocker on its own, but coverage pattern differs |
| Footprint stamps full drone sphere as `Empty` before plan | `markDroneFootprintEmpty` with `radius < grid_resolution` stamps **only center cell** | Neighbors not cleared → movement still blocked |
| Planning only runs after local space is proven clear | Planning runs after orientations are exhausted; `isSpherePassable` is the gate | Start position not passable → `findPath` fails → explore/unstick skipped → `FinishedWithUnmappableVoxels` with 1% mapped |
| Rescans allowed as long as there's unknown space | `last_scan_made_progress = false` after a no-progress pass kills retry chain | Map 99% unknown, algorithm quits after 2 passes |

**Symptom:** mission reports `COMPLETED` or `FinishedWithUnmappableVoxels` in ~26 steps, `mission_score ≈ 0.55`, output map has ~6 non-`Unmapped` voxels.

**Not a symptom of:** bad scorer, bad map conversion, or CI failure (CI only checks `score >= 0`).

## Validation rule (not optional)

After any algorithm change, **always** run scenario 3 manually and inspect both score and mapped voxel count:

```bash
./build/drone_mapper_simulation scenarios/composition_scenario3.yaml /tmp/out3
grep mission_score /tmp/out3/simulation_output.yaml
./build/maps_comparison data_maps/scenario_3_map.npy /tmp/out3/output_results/run_0001/output_map.npy
```

A meaningful port produces a score significantly above 0 and a drone that actually traverses the map. "Tests pass" is not sufficient — tests assert `score >= 0` only.
